<p><b>Melville Louis Kossuth (Melvil) Dewey</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1851-12-10"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="12-10"><a href="/wiki/December_10" title="December 10">December 10</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1851" title="1851">1851</a></span>–<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1931-12-26"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="12-26"><a href="/wiki/December_26" title="December 26">December 26</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1931" title="1931">1931</a></span>) was an American <a href="/wiki/Librarian" title="Librarian">librarian</a> and <a href="/wiki/Educator" title="Educator" class="mw-redirect">educator</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/Inventor" title="Inventor">inventor</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Dewey_Decimal_Classification" title="Dewey Decimal Classification">Dewey Decimal Classification</a> system of <a href="/wiki/Library_classification" title="Library classification">library classification</a>.</p>
